<h2>Installation</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="#requirements" title="WalkerCMS Requirements">Requirements</a></li>
  <li><a href="#installation" title="Installing WalkerCMS">Installation</a></li>
  <li><a href="#postintall" title="After Installation">After Installation</a></li>
</ul>

<h3><a name="requirements"></a>Requirements</h3>
<p>In addition to the following software, this documentation assumes a familiarity of HTML, Javascript,
   PHP, Apache, and your OS (both development and production).</p>
<ul>
  <li>Apache or another compatible web server.</li>
  <li>PHP 5.3+.</li>
  <li>
    <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/fileinfo.installation.php" title="FileInfo extension">FileInfo</a>
    extension for PHP.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/mcrypt.installation.php" title="Mcrypt extension">Mcrypt</a>
    extension for PHP.
  </li>
</ul>
<p>Additionally, a <acronym title="user interface">UI</acronym> testing engine is provided and requires
   the following:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a hrev="http://www.microsoft.com/visualstudio/eng/visual-studio-update" title="Visual Studio">Visual Studio 2010</a> or later (Express Editions will work just fine)</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.nunit.org/" title="NUnit">NUnit</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://seleniumhq.org/" title="Selenium">Selenium</a> with WebDriver</li>
</ul>
<p class="back-to-top"><a href="#top" title="Back to top">Back to top</a></p>

<h3><a name="installation"></a>Installation</h3>
<ol>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/tpwalke2/walkercms/zipball/master" title="WalkerCMS source">Download WalkerCMS</a>.</li>
  <li>Extract the archive to a directory accessible to your webserver.</li>
</ol>
<p>There are a couple of options available to you at this point: start from scratch or use WalkerCMS.net
(this website) as an example and modify it to suit.</p>
<h4>From scratch</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Create a directory that is a sibling to the directory where you extracted WalkerCMS.</li>
  <li>Copy the contents of <root path of WalkerCMS>/WalkerCMS/defaults to the directory you just created.</li>
  <li>Create a &quot;storage&quot; subdirectory in the directory you created in step 1.</li>
</ol>
<h4>Modify WalkerCMS.net</h4>
<ol>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/tpwalke2/walkercms.net/zipball/master" title="WalkerCMS.net source">Download WalkerCMS.net</a> (this website).</li>
  <li>Extract the archive to a directory that is a sibling to the WalkerCMS directory.</li>
</ol>
<h4><a name="directory-structure"></a>Directory Structure</h4>
<p>Ensure that the final directory structure for either of the above options is as follows:</p>
<code><pre>
/root/
   |-> WalkerCMS/
   |       |-> laravel/
   |       |-> WalkerCMS/
   |
   |-> WalkerCMS.net (or your site directory)
           |-> public/
           |     |-> images/ **
           |     |-> scripts/
           |     |-> styles/
           |
           |-> sitespecific/
           |     |-> content/
           |     |-> footers/ **
           |     |-> headers/ **
           |     |-> htmlheaders/ **
           |     |-> nav/ **
           |     |-> secondarycontent/ **
           |     |-> subnav/ **
           |     |-> template/
           |
           |-> storage/
                 |-> cache/
                 |-> logs/
                 |-> views/
</pre></code>
<p>Directories marked with ** are optional.</p>
<p class="back-to-top"><a href="#top" title="Back to top">Back to top</a></p>

